signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: write file on Windows
    namespace: host-interaction/file-system/write
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
    scope: function
    mbc:
      - File System::Writes File [C0052]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-04.exe_:0x4011FC

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potential System Information Discovery Via Wmic.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the use of the WMI command-line (WMIC) utility to identify and display various system information,
including OS, CPU, GPU, and disk drive names; memory capacity; display resolution; and baseboard, BIOS,
and GPU driver products/versions.
Some of these commands were used by Aurora Stealer in late 2022/early 2023.
Detects the conhost execution as parent process. Can be used to evaded defense mechanism.
Detects requests to exclude files, folders or processes from Antivirus scanning using PowerShell cmdlets
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
